25:54.011 --> 25:57.732
<i>It's a hand-cranked,
horse-drawn world.</i>

25:59.141 --> 26:03.988
<i>That's the guy we came to see,
the one with the crazy mustache.</i>

26:04.146 --> 26:06.990
<i>He's a math teacher
named Augustin Mouchot.</i>

26:07.566 --> 26:13.118
<i>Remember, it's 1878,
this is a world lit mostly by gaslight.</i>

26:13.280 --> 26:15.408
<i>The automobile is still years away.</i>

26:16.492 --> 26:21.168
<i>But Mouchot here is dazzling the crowd
with his solar power concentrator.</i>

26:23.916 --> 26:26.465
The sun belongs to all of us.

26:26.627 --> 26:33.181
Even though it is 150 million kilometers
away from us, feel its awesome power.

26:33.342 --> 26:36.767
My invention concentrates
the free energy of the sun...

26:36.929 --> 26:39.808
...and converts it into mechanical motion.

26:39.973 --> 26:42.601
It can power any kind of machine.

26:42.768 --> 26:46.864
It can produce electricity
or run a printing press...

26:47.022 --> 26:49.150
...or make ice on a hot day.

26:52.694 --> 26:53.786
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS IN FRENCH)</font>

26:53.946 --> 26:55.948
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHATTERING)</font>

27:04.123 --> 27:08.378
Ha-ha-ha! Think of it,
sunlight converted into ice.

27:08.544 --> 27:11.639
You see, my friends,
what wonders we can work...

27:11.797 --> 27:14.391
...if we harness the bounteous energy
of the sun.

27:15.384 --> 27:18.228
The world will someday run out of coal.

27:18.387 --> 27:22.483
But the magnificent sun
will always be there for us.

27:37.072 --> 27:39.916
Mouchot took home
the gold medal from the fair.

27:40.075 --> 27:42.749
But the price of coal tumbled,
becoming so cheap...

27:42.911 --> 27:45.334
...that there was no
interest in solar energy.

27:45.497 --> 27:50.970
Besides, no one understood back then what
the true cost was of burning fossil fuel.

27:51.128 --> 27:54.098
Mouchot's research funding was cut off.

27:54.423 --> 27:58.018
Thirty-five years later,
in the early years of the 20th century...

27:58.177 --> 28:01.272
...another door opened
to an alternative future.

28:01.430 --> 28:05.560
It happened in Egypt,
on the banks of the Nile.

28:14.818 --> 28:17.446
<i><font color="#808080">TYSON :</font>
Memo to future time travelers.</i>

28:17.613 --> 28:22.744
<i>This would be an excellent entry point
for averting climate change.</i>

28:23.118 --> 28:25.962
<i>Egypt, 1913.</i>

28:26.121 --> 28:29.341
<i>That's Frank Shuman of Philadelphia.</i>

28:30.751 --> 28:33.300
<i>He's only had three years of schooling...</i>

28:33.462 --> 28:37.592
<i>...but his genius for innovation
