<i>The Apollo missions to the moon
were an extension of the arms race...</i>

33:33.595 --> 33:35.222
<i>...that raged between them.</i>

33:36.932 --> 33:39.902
<i>Sending people to orbit the Earth
or go to the moon...</i>

33:40.060 --> 33:43.314
<i>...requires big, reliable,
powerful rockets...</i>

33:43.480 --> 33:45.653
<i>...precisely the same
technology you need...</i>

33:45.815 --> 33:49.115
<i>...to carry a nuclear warhead
halfway around the planet...</i>

33:49.277 --> 33:52.577
<i>...to destroy your enemy's largest cities.</i>

33:55.116 --> 33:59.792
<i><font color="#808080">KENNEDY :</font> I believe that this nation should
commit itself to achieving the goal...</i>

33:59.955 --> 34:01.957
<i>...before this decade is out...</i>

34:02.123 --> 34:06.924
<i>...of landing a man on the moon
and returning him safely to the Earth.</i>

34:07.379 --> 34:12.101
<i><font color="#808080">TYSON :</font> President Kennedy's 1961 speech
electrified the nation...</i>

34:12.259 --> 34:15.889
<i>...and it contained
much that was remarkably prophetic...</i>

34:16.054 --> 34:20.150
<i>...but not a word about a scientific
objective for going to the moon.</i>

34:20.308 --> 34:22.310
<i>No questions about the moon's origin...</i>

34:22.476 --> 34:25.525
<i>...or the hope of bringing back samples
to analyze.</i>

34:25.688 --> 34:28.283
<i>No, the Apollo missions were conceived...</i>

34:28.440 --> 34:34.164
<i>...as a demonstration of the superior power
and precision of our strategic missiles.</i>

34:34.322 --> 34:38.418
<i>But a funny thing happened to us
on our way to the moon.</i>

34:39.703 --> 34:41.330
<i>We looked homeward...</i>

34:41.496 --> 34:43.793
<i>...and discovered another world...</i>

34:43.956 --> 34:45.333
<i>...OUT OWfi.</i>

