<i>For the first time
we inhabitants of Earth...</i>

34:48.295 --> 34:51.764
<i>...could step back and
see it as it really is.</i>

34:51.922 --> 34:58.021
<i>One world, indivisible,
and kind of small in the cosmic context.</i>

34:59.014 --> 35:02.564
<i>Whatever the reason we first mustered
the enormous resources required...</i>

35:02.726 --> 35:04.273
...for the Apollo program...

35:04.436 --> 35:09.033
<i>...however mired it was in Cold War
nationalism and the instruments of death...</i>

35:09.608 --> 35:14.034
<i>...the inescapable recognition
of the unity and fragility of the Earth...</i>

35:14.195 --> 35:16.744
<i>...is its clear and luminous dividend...</i>

35:16.906 --> 35:19.079
<i>...the unexpected gift of Apollo.</i>

35:19.242 --> 35:22.291
<i>A project conceived in
